The government has committed Sh13.4 billion for the implementation of the Digital Literacy Programme.Broadcasting and Telecommunication PS Sammy Itemere said they plan to complete the DLP implementation by the end of this fiscal year.He said part of the programme will cover completion of the laptop project in all 23,000 public primary schools. Itemere said more than 800,000 laptops have been distributed.He spoke on Thursday while inspecting the installation of laptops at MM Shah and Kondele primary schools.As we move towards achieving Vision 2030, the government is committed to building an informed citizenry through digitisation, Itemere said.&ldquo;The laptops [will] ensure that the children, upon [reaching] maturity become more innovative,&rdquo; he said.